Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Because somebody Ozu referred to as "Master"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.00,0:05:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lives on the second floor of this boarding house, and it seems Ozu comes to visit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.43,0:05:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I surmised that he was probably a master of lewd jokes or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.89,0:05:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyebrows are raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.62,0:05:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why so tense?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.77,0:05:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! I have no interest in wasting my time like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.81,0:05:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How cruel. I put a lot of effort into enjoying wasting my college years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.36,0:05:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you have no right to criticize me on that front.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.73,0:05:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.03,0:05:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold me back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God damn him...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:49.58,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(400,0)\bord2\c&H000000&\fnBurst My Bubble\frz51.702\3c&HC0E7E5&\move(354,156,332,195,0,2109)}Bicycle Club
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.95,0:05:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In there was written a cornucopia of information about all possible kinds of aerodynamic bicycle parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.17,0:05:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no physical strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.59,0:06:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, how about I battle with the specs of my bicycle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it not a path of escape, even for someone weak like myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.47,0:06:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having seen the light, in my second year I embarked on a complete change of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking back on it now, it was only the beginning of yet greater unhappiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.73,0:06:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting your hands on a good bicycle takes money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.92,0:06:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A reduction by a mere gram or two requires an immense amount of funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lightening the wheels, tires, and shoes.\NThe handlebar, stem, compact crank.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.44,0:06:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to obtain a somewhat decent bicycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.50,0:06:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put my studies aside and dove into every part-time job there was,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.00,0:06:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even dabbling in some illegal work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.08,0:06:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I became nothing more than a hoarding fiend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And finally, in the winter of my second year,\Ntaking loans from my friends and acquaintances,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.71,0:06:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got my hands on the full-spec machine I had been dreaming of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.59,0:06:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What lightness!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.84,0:06:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This bike is, indeed, my wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.92,0:06:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt that I could fly anywhere with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.05,0:06:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I had already heard the rumors of the Cheerful Cleanup Corps,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I took extreme caution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.76,0:06:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so enamored with my new bicycle,\NI'd take her out with me wherever I went.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.65,0:07:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about this, Manami.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.49,0:07:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had only let my guard down for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't expected the Cleanup Corps to go to such lengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.62,0:07:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would never see my beloved wheels again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.41,0:07:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this who I am now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the two years I have left, will I stay such a weakling?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.09,0:07:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could not shut my eyes from that reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't stand to look upon it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.93,0:07:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gone nuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.65,0:07:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.28,0:07:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, I have seen the error of my ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.15,0:07:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had lost sight of something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bought two years ago at the university co-op,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my Manami had been with me through all my joys and sorrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, once mad with visions of road bikes, would no longer be led astray.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami is for me, my true life-partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:01.83,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\c&H42476D&\pos(655,55)\fad(200,0)}Shimanami Cup
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.00,0:08:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But fate soon tore Manami and I apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.79,0:08:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami... Have you seen my Manami?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.74,0:08:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't considered it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems Manami hadn't been considered a participating bike,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.01,0:08:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had been transported to the finish line by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.89,0:08:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the time I'd figured that out, a great deal of time had passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.89,0:08:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I started the race four hours late, long after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.31,0:08:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shimanami Cup goes from Onomichi to Shikoku, crossing the bridges from island to island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.23,0:08:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After crossing one bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.48,0:08:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you run along the island's coastline, then climb up another bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.48,0:08:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's a strenuous up-down course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami, why must you be so heavy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.41,0:08:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where all the other racers are?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.85,0:08:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or wait, is the race even still going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.25,0:08:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.49,0:08:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? There are still people out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.18,0:08:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need any entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.72,0:08:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though my only goal now was to stay on the course,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as night fell I began to lose sight of the course indicators.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.85,0:08:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For what reason was I racing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:08:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For what reason did I even go to college?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:08:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami? What the hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.06,0:09:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a cheap-ass basket-bike!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.44,0:09:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Continuing with the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.77,0:09:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Today in Hiroshima prefecture, the tenth annual Shimanami Cup was held in Onomichi city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The 240 participants put on a fierce race,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and the winner, finishing with a splendid victory, was Kyoto's Higuchi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.54,0:09:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the crystallization of my past two years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.00,0:09:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.00,0:09:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}"I worked hard for this day."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}"I'm very happy I could be victorious for my disciple who always cheered me on," he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, enough! I'm going home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where had all this energy I'd expended the whole time vanished to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This violates the conservation of energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does not compute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.47,0:09:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this not blasphemous to modern physics?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While I was thinking of such things, morning dawned, then night fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.02,0:09:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then morning again, then night, and when I came to, I had reached Kiyamachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.15,0:09:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your face is a face of extreme impatience... You are unsatisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.17,0:10:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can sense your fiercely earnest talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly did I tip my hat to the old woman's keen insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.46,0:10:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I sense there is an opportunity you can't let pass by.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.88,0:10:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Opportunity?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.79,0:10:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This opportunity is always dangling in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please grab it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.17,0:10:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be 3,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.93,0:10:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You raised the prices again? Damn, that was quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed that I had somehow fallen into the sea of worthlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.77,0:10:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps I had never even taken off to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I was fated to waste away my college life, just as Ozu had said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.87,0:10:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for abducting you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking you to my circle's shack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.34,0:10:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a serious favor to ask of you, Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.21,0:10:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san was a student in the engineering department one year below me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous year, she had been the only female registered in Soleil,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.18,0:11:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and amazingly won the overall victory at a road race held in Keage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to use the prize money for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason for me to answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had sturdy legs and an air that didn't let others get near her,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.69,0:11:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she had no real interest in races, and quit Soleil.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She invested all the prize money in her current circle, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.12,0:11:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for the shady look of the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.97,0:11:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You? You're the dropout from Soleil?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.78,0:11:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.80,0:11:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our club president.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, you really do have a feeble body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.27,0:11:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly the kind of man perfect to become a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.60,0:11:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Become a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.98,0:11:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to our Birdman Team!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.57,0:11:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weight, 59 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chest, 80 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.95,0:12:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waist, 70 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.62,0:12:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, you have the ideal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.20,0:12:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-kun is our star engineer, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.27,0:12:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she seems to be interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.92,0:12:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We almost have the airframe completed, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but no one in the team is suitable to pilot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.47,0:12:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't have to do anything in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So will you pilot it, with that perfect body you have right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.60,0:12:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to get in that plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.68,0:12:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm a complete weakling. I even dropped out of Soleil...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.46,0:12:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need our pilot to be as frail as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.77,0:12:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's not all, but you're definitely our ideal pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.03,0:12:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't need any special training.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.74,0:12:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simply come to the competition as you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.37,0:12:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just take care of your body so you don't get the flu, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.21,0:12:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a sudden development.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.09,0:12:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It felt a bit like I was being forced; like a nice way of saying I'd be dropped into a lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Birdman contest is a cruel game where you pedal and pedal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until you inevitably drop into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.54,0:13:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't have to be me. They could've used anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.39,0:13:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And isn't it scary to go straight into the sea from that height?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unbearable. I can't take losing anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.36,0:13:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was spring of last year, during the road race at Keage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had taken off at a good speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I immediately became winded, and stared up at the canal incline.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power plant over there is quite wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.35,0:13:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of dubious machines, and stirs up my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's especially lovely during the cherry blossom season.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san, shouldn't you be in a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.53,0:13:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the favorite to win the women's race?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.71,0:13:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll be off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cherry blossoms are very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.89,0:13:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so Akashi-san won not only the woman's race, but the overall victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:13:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, I saw the Mochiguman dangling from Akashi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.76,0:13:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They come in sets of five, so it seemed like she had lost one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.60,0:14:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, I came across it, and continually forgot to return it until today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.77,0:14:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This opportunity is always dangling in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.74,0:14:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This body has already crashed once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.28,0:14:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Falling is something I have firsthand knowledge of.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.72,0:14:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I need to do is grit my teeth and launch with a shout.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.49,0:14:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Akashi-san will surely come to me after I've fallen, with a smile on her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.10,0:14:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, I'll sit behind Akashi-san as she rides up the cherry blossom-lined incline!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.17,0:14:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Can I allow myself to be addled by such feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.59,0:14:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your dreams shouldn't be so flimsy, weak, and limp-noodled!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really okay to lower my goal to such a shameless fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.26,0:14:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To no longer shoot for the Sun, and live lazily on the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.18,0:14:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is that Icarus?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.14,0:14:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd just be some kid with ugly-ass wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.93,0:14:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wavering in the gap between reality and fantasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.98,0:14:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,exhausted by the tumultuous developments of the past few days
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.94,0:14:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my restless, sleepless return from Shikoku,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.44,0:14:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fell asleep like a sack of potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.83,0:14:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you keep up with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.08,0:14:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This man is named Jougasaki,\Nand is president of the movie circle "Misogi."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.66,0:14:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a man that lives for working out and women's breasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked him to teach me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.29,0:14:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, I'd made my decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.75,0:14:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd fly farther than anyone, higher than anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.17,0:14:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at the dawn of my victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san will be sitting on the back of Minami as we ride up the cherry blossom-lined incline!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.76,0:15:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up. Victory is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.45,0:15:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not allow you to run from a battle and live aloof like that guy, Higuchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're a man, then grab victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grab victory, and grab women's tits!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.06,0:15:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jougasaki-senpai's teachings were actually pretty clear-cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.27,0:15:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my motivation rose to higher and higher levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Birdman contest was even televised, and the ideal place for the circle to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.63,0:15:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I won, then I would no doubt gain the attention
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.19,0:15:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of raven-haired maidens from all over Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.32,0:15:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet I'd need to broaden my field of vision to women other than just Akashi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.95,0:15:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is a trial all winners must face!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being the hero sure is tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.97,0:15:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.03,0:15:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said you were fine the way you were!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now you've got muscles!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.93,0:15:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.08,0:15:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:16:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-kun's plane is designed with extremely sensitive aviation tolerances!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.61,0:16:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even a 10-gram difference in the pilot would mean redoing the entire blueprint!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.03,0:16:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruined! It's all ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.22,0:16:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough! Akashi-kun, you be the pilot after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and your muscles can get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.33,0:16:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I already had my hands full thinking up countermeasures to the Cleanup Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.71,0:16:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-kun, you hurry back to work too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.26,0:16:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for getting you involved in this weird stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.51,0:16:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, too, for not living up to your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.35,0:16:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Actually, the problem was that you far surpassed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.73,0:16:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Birdman is, after all, an absurd goal that goes against the reason of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.52,0:16:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I was thinking that the pilot should be a person
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a soul charred by idleness and wasted passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.99,0:16:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that after you finished the Shimanami Cup on a basket-bike,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.37,0:16:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you came all the way back from Shikoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.08,0:16:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an incredible waste of energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, that wasn't exactly my intent...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I asked you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.04,0:17:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the idea that you'd go so far as to train didn't figure into my calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.30,0:17:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I still have a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.39,0:17:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, but I have to redo the design now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.70,0:17:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.50,0:17:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I had come to the Keage Incline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.21,0:17:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had prayed to come here with Akashi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.34,0:17:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now I felt like my rose-colored campus life was slipping even farther away,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.18,0:17:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my heart wept within.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:17:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'd be better off flowing down
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.36,0:18:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and trying to make my name as an egg-pumpkin spirit that lives in Lake Biwa...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.48,0:18:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Cleanup Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.69,0:18:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man in the trench coat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.57,0:18:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.75,0:18:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, you caught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.50,0:18:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it a secret, 'kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.54,0:18:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an important source of funds for the Secret Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.88,0:18:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Akashi-san's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.63,0:18:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in a recession, so bicycles alone aren't cutting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.43,0:18:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A certain person up north is looking for a plane much like this to play with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.76,0:18:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just going to crash into Lake Biwa anyway, so this is a far better use, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.81,0:18:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what about my bike?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.73,0:18:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one that stole it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.73,0:18:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really concern myself with each one individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.82,0:18:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's how I show my love, so grab it while you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.97,0:18:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it doesn't matter which path you take,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.95,0:18:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll keep ending up right where you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.70,0:19:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be so bad to give yourself up and go with the flow?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're connected by the black thread of fate, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got debts, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.48,0:19:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go around Kyoto collecting bicycles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only if I can aim mainly at couples riding two to a bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing! You do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.19,0:19:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.48,0:19:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the jig's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.11,0:19:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Akashi-san is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.69,0:19:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell anyone about the Cleanup Corps, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.73,0:19:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might be bad for your health....
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.90,0:19:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.78,0:19:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the trenchcoat man from the Cycle Cleanup Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.29,0:19:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! That's not it! Akashi-san, this is a misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.05,0:19:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it, the Cheery Cycle Cleanup Corps are actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.80,0:20:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Explain it to me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.06,0:20:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.03,0:20:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, where are the brakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.49,0:20:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.66,0:20:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.70,0:20:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jump off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.87,0:20:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate I'll crash into the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.79,0:20:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice but to try pedaling to fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.46,0:20:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time for my training to pay off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.21,0:20:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.47,0:20:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the pedals?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.10,0:20:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san, where are the pedals?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.22,0:20:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.06,0:20:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the free-flying category!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:20:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It finally dawned on me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:20:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that this was all a truly wasted effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.07,0:21:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this all started from the moment I'd considered the cycling club.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.18,0:21:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had joined some other circle, I would have surely spent quite a different two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.64,0:21:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meeting Ozu was clearly the greatest catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could Icarus have ridden the wind,\Nhad he not tried so hard to flap his wings?
